main event: On July 3, 1959, witnesses observed a bright point of light moving from North to South at a high speed near Williams, Wisconsin.
interesting points: The object appeared at approximately 20 degrees in elevation.,It was about the size of a star, steady and white in color.,The object traveled at an estimated 1,500 mph for about 5 seconds before disappearing.,No sound was associated with the sighting.,The sighting might have been an aircraft reflecting sunlight.
sighted object: a bright point of light in the sky
witness description: DF, WFF, and other USAF personnel
